Package: pestRisk
Type: Package
Title: Modelling Current Agricultural Pest Invasion Risk Using SDMs
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2026-06-07
Authors@R: c(
    person("Meriem", "Choukri", email = "meriem.choukri@iav.ac.ma",
       role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A complete, reproducible toolkit for modelling the current
    distribution and invasion risk of agricultural pests. Implements a
    full pipeline: download of GBIF occurrence data and WorldClim bioclimatic
    variables, spatial data cleaning, variable selection (Pearson correlation
    and VIF stepwise elimination), species distribution modelling (Random
    Forest and MaxEnt via maxnet), risk-map generation classified into
    low/medium/high categories, country-level risk summaries, and automatic
    HTML/PDF reporting. Targeted at three major pest species: Spodoptera
    frugiperda (fall armyworm), Tuta absoluta (tomato leafminer), and
    Ceratitis capitata (Mediterranean fruit fly). Designed to support
    phytosanitary surveillance and agricultural risk assessment.
